established in 74% of patients with four patients complaining of dysphagia. 
Speech was restored using an electrolarynx or Blom Singer valve in 70% of 
patients. Most patients required radiotherapy as part of their adjuvant 
treatment. In our hands the JFF for reconstruction following 
pharyngolaryngoesophageal resection allows restoration of function following 
major ablative surgery.

